1. Generate a unique ID for each authorized mobile device: When an authorized device accesses your website for the first time, you can generate a unique ID and store it in a server-side database.
2. Set a cookie on the authorized device: When the authorized device visits your website, you can set a cookie on the device that includes the unique ID. This can be done using JavaScript code on your website.
3. Check for the cookie on subsequent visits: On subsequent visits, you can check for the cookie on the device. If the cookie exists and contains a valid ID, you can allow access to your website.

Here is some sample code that shows how to set a cookie with a unique device ID using JavaScript:
```javascript
// Generate a unique ID for the device
