To retrieve the cookie value using JavaScript, you can use the `document.cookie` property. This property returns a string that contains all the cookies for the current website, separated by semicolons. You can then split this string into an array of individual cookies and loop through the array to find the cookie you are looking for.

Here is some sample code that shows how to retrieve the cookie value with the name "deviceId":
```javascript
// Function to get the value of a cookie by name
function getCookieValue(name) {
  var cookies = document.cookie.split(';');
  for (var i = 0; i < cookies.length; i++) {
    var cookie = cookies[i].trim();
    if (cookie.indexOf(name + '=') === 0) {
      return cookie.substring(name.length + 1);
    }
  }
  return null;
}

