To use the Wistia Uploader in an Angular 14 project, you can follow these steps:

1. Install the Wistia uploader package:
```java
npm install @wistia/uploader
```
2. Import the `UploaderModule` in your `app.module.ts`:
```python
import { UploaderModule } from '@wistia/uploader';

@NgModule({
  imports: [
    UploaderModule
  ]
})
export class AppModule { }
```
3. In your component where you want to use the uploader, you can import the `UploaderService` and use it to create an instance of the uploader:
```typescript
import { Component } from '@angular/core';
import { UploaderService } from '@wistia/uploader';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-my-component',
  template: `
    <button (click)="openUploader()">Open Uploader</button>
  `
})
export class MyComponent {
  constructor(private uploaderService: UploaderService) {}

  openUploader() {
    const uploader = this.uploaderService.create();
    uploader.show();
  }
}
```
4. You can then use the `uploader` instance to interact with the uploader. For example, you can listen for events:
```typescript
import { Component } from '@angular/core';
import { UploaderService } from '@wistia/uploader';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-my-component',
  template: `
    <button (click)="openUploader()">Open Uploader</button>
  `
})
export class MyComponent {
  constructor(private uploaderService: UploaderService) {}

  openUploader() {
    const uploader = this.uploaderService.create();
    uploader.on('uploadsuccess', (file, response) => {
      console.log('File uploaded successfully!');
      console.log(response);
    });
    uploader.show();
  }
}
```
These are just some basic examples to get you started. You can find more information about the Wistia Uploader in the official documentation: <https://wistia.com/support/developers/upload-api-v3>

