    @GET("/api/MediaStorage/GetCookies")
    suspend fun getCookies(): ResponseBody

}
```
1. In your activity or fragment, make a call to the `getCookies()` function using Retrofit and extract the cookies. Here is an example of how you can do it:
```kotlin
val retrofit = Retrofit.Builder()
    .baseUrl("https://your-api-url.com")
    .build()

val apiService = retrofit.create(ApiService::class.java)
val cookies = apiService.getCookies().headers().get("Set-Cookie")
```
1. Add the cookies and Key-Pair-Id query parameter or cookie value to the `PlayerConfig` object when initializing the Castlabs player. Here is an example of how you can do it:
```css
