Using a `HashSet` to store the keys allows us to perform lookups in constant time, regardless of the size of the input list. Therefore, the time complexity of this implementation is O(n), where n is the number of `Data` objects in the input list. This is a significant improvement over the nested loop approach, especially for large input sizes.

